Pull through the crux start without any pro for 15 feet (or clip the bolt). Once through the start, climb easier holds to the overhanging section and better pro. Pull through the overhanging section and find some long reachy slopers at the top.

name: Pandora's Box
description: Sport Route

name: Puckered Green
description: This climb was originally done on gear and given the poor pro at the top, had quite the finish.  In the time since its first ascent, it saw very little traffic and became so green it was virtually unclimbable.  During the re-equip, we spent two days cleaning this face and then, because of misinformation at the time, it was decided to put bolts on this route.  At least now with the bolt protection, hopefully the climb will see some traffic and stay reasonably clean.  Start left of the roof and climb up the obvious vertical line.

name: Undercling Fling
description: Start on the obvious ledge.  Climb up passing 3 bolts to the cold shuts.  Slightly overhanging and sloping at the top.  Crux at finish.  May need brushed at the top (well worth the effort).  Probably hasn't been climbed recently.  Very good climb when brushed.

name: A Flash in the Pan
description: Climb the face about 10' in from the left edge. A highstep start and slopers make this one an interesting route.

name: Campus Corner
description: This is a very short climb, but very fun!  Start at the low overhang at the base of the obvious arete of Cave World.  Make good use of jugs and heel hooks and look for the refrigerator door handle near the top.  You can place some gear in the lower horizontals or just stick clip the bolt.

name: Chop Chop
description: Start under the large roof at its far right end. Work out the roof to a jug at the lip. Heel hook and reach left for a pocket to gain access to the horizontal at the midpoint of the climb. Finish on slopers and edges above.

name: Mr. Bill's Bolts
description: Climb the route 2' left of the arete past 2 bolts to the top. Route #8 in the 2019 guide.

name: Chimney Sweep
description: Fun easy chimney climbing in the middle of the corridor.  There are Mussy Hooks to use to set a top rope on this.

name: From Mexico with Love
description: A route that starts on the left side of the arete that is to the left to 'Lame Duck'.  Climb the face left of the arete until you meet the constriction of the chimney, then get creative! Originally rated 5.6, but consensus is that it is a couple of grades harder.

name: Lame Duck
description: Climb the face with a bunch of arete moves. Balance-y if done direct, but can be done much easier with laybacks off of SBR block which knocks it down two full grades. Route #3 on Chimney Block in the 2019 guide.

name: Lumberjack
description: Short section with ledges that take pro leads up to the first bolt. Commit to the face and power to the top anchors.

name: Beginners Edge
description: Climb the tricky arete up past 2 bolts to a fun top out.

name: Climbing on Rainbows
description: Climb to the right of the tree (the face directly in front of you when jumping from the rock to the root). Climb up the right side to the horizontal. Traverse to the left on the horizontal. Climb directly up the face to the top.

name: Dirty Bird
description: Start directly across from "Into the Light." Climb up the large holds to a right facing flake. Finish above.

name: Dyno Sore
description: Climb up through the overhanging arete. Work your way to the top using the arete and some holds to the right face.

name: Face Up To It
description: Climb the thin overhanging face to a tricky undercling move that will provide access to the large ledge and the top out to the right.

name: Face Value
description: Start on the right side arete of the block. Climb friction and thin face holds to a horizontal rest. Move left and continue to top. Balance is the key to this climb.

name: Into the Light
description: Face climb up clean rock to tricky move left and a balancy move to finish. Stiff for the grade.

name: Mickey Mantle
description: Start in the corridor 5' right of "Climbing on Rainbows."  Climb face to small ramp then straight up to top.

name: Shapeshifter
description: This route can be climbed as a chimney (5.7), a layback using the opposite wall (5.8), or as a face climb without the opposite wall (5.10).

name: The Thinker
description: Climb the short, thin slabby face up the center of the wall.

name: First Crack at It
description: Climb the obvious wide crack near the right end of this wall. #5 on Crack Wall on 2019 guide.

name: Mr. Bill
description: Climb the crack in the center of this face. Route #7 in the 2019 guide.

name: Not So Secure Left
description: The first problem on the Crack Wall.

name: Not So Secure Right
description: Across from the Ocean Wall.

name: Orange Crush
description: Climb the face route 4' right of the big crack. #6 on Crack Wall on 2019 guide.

name: Cherry Top
description: This route takes great gear in the bottom crack where the climbing is not more than 5.8.  The crux is at the top and well protected with the single bolt on the climb.  It is a very nice mixed climb.

name: Encroachment
description: Sport Route

name: Grand Central
description: Crux is in the middle of the route.  Fun and sustained.

name: Hearty
description: Fun sport route that shares anchors with "Make Over."

name: Huck Yeah!
description: Sport Route

name: In the Think of It
description: Crux is at bulge.

name: Make Over
description: Sport Route

name: Pumper
description: Start about 10 ft to the right of the left side of the main face.  Climb up a shallow arete, then head a bit left, then straight up.   Nothing but jugs, but fairly pumpy.

name: Stemosis
description: Around the corner and to the left of Pumper is a deceiving climb. Start on easy ledges to gain the base of a large offwidth on your left. Steeeem across and reach overhead to pull the crux finish.

name: Swarm
description: Climb the obvious right facing flake to the top.

name: Tic-Tac
description: This route feels tight.  The tree is close to you and the moves feel hard. This is my least favorite on this wall.

name: Boss Man Brooks
description: Start below the dihedral on the horizontals. Climb up to the dihedral and follow to the top.

name: Mr. Good Climb
description: Climb directly up the arete using holds on both the left and right face.

name: Yosemicrack
description: Climb the obvious crack 8' right of the arete.  Follow to top.

name: Tidal Wave
description: Start below the left line of bolts.  Climb up passing mostly positive holds.  As you approach the shuts, the holds get bigger.  The route tends to get a bit dirty toward the anchors.

name: Tsunami
description: This route climbs much like a boulder problem.   And with it's short stature, you could probably protect it with a few pads if you like.  Start below the right line of bolts.  Find some nice finger locks and crimps to clip the first bolt.   Make a reachy move to a sloping horizontal to clip the 2nd bolt(crux).   Continue straight up to reach the bolt anchors on the top or head slightly left and lower off the drop in shuts above Tidal Wave.   Use some caution near the top, some of the holds are a bit crispy.

name: Backscratcher
description: Start left side of the tree. Move right getting marginal gear. Squeeze between the tree and the rock through the crux moves and gain the wide flake on the right of the tree. Fun gear placements. Finish at anchors.

name: Drill Queen
description: Reachy start for shorter people (stack some rocks). Easier climbing once established on climb. A very popular Lost Crag route. This route was originally give a 5.4 rating but consensus is that it is at least a few grades harder.

name: H.O.S.C. Variation (AKA Who Needs Pro)
description: Sport Route

name: Hang on St. Christopher
description: Start just left of arete.  Climb up using slopers, etc following the line of 3 bolts.  Avoid starting around the corner on Who needs pro 5.4 trad.  This seriously downgrades the route to about 5.7.  Finish at Metolius Shuts.

name: Long Live the Klingons
description: Climb directly up to the roof. Pull the overhang on the left side and finish on the thin face above.  Originally graded 10b, consensus is that this is a 5.11.

name: Michael's Easy Ten
description: Sport Route

name: Preacher Norm
description: Start just right of the low roof off of the ground. Climb up and move left to the clean steep face. Climb the face and arete to the top.  As per SWPACC Guide - Must have 24" slings to lower off.

name: SBR Left
description: Trad Route

name: SBR Right
description: Climb directly up from the start of Backscratcher to the top.

name: Tip and Tap
description: Right sport route on this face.  Bolted in 2008 by unknown parties.  Originally a Top Roped route, now a clip up.  Enjoy.

name: Evil Edge
description: This is one of the nicest routes at the grade at The Lost Crag. Climb up the blocky start, avoiding the large ledge to the left. Head for the clean arete, gaining a stance at its base. Use the arete to make a reachy move to the very positive top edge. Top it out.

name: Hang On Slopey
description: Climb a line 6' right of Slopers in the Rain. Climb up dirty, but useful handholds placing resonable protection on the way. Exit to the left at the top. Route #5 on Short Stack on 2019 guide.

name: Left Arete
description: Start at the low overhang under the arete to the left of Reunion.  Climb up to reach a jug and horizontal crack about half way up.  Plug some gear here.  Gain a stance, reach for the lip and top it out.  The top out is interesting.

name: Psycho Driller
description: Follows the wandering line of 3 bolts up the back side of The Short Stack. This climb was bolted on lead by Norm Reed to gain access to the top of the block. Popular route at the Lost Crag.

name: rap station
description: rap rings for descent

name: Reunion
description: This is a great route for the Lost Crag.  Fairly continuous climbing.  Start on some small holds to reach a nice flake and reach for the large horizontal.  Place some gear here.  Reach up to a 2 finger pocket, pull up to gain a stance and clip the bolt.  Now the crux begins...all the way to the finish.  The last moves are very reminiscent of the New River Gorge.

name: Rise and Whine
description: Climb the face up to a large horizontal and place some gear. Heel hook and crank/ lunge to the crescent shaped ledge. Follow the flake past the bolt to the top.

name: Slope Stone Left
description: This is the left variation of Slope Stone

name: Slope Stone Right
description: This route was originally done as a trad route up the obvious dihedral.  Bolts were added for safety and to also increase traffic on this fun line.

name: Slopers in the Rain
description: Start 10' right of Unnamed 5.9 trad route using the obvious holds directly to the top.

name: teaching station
description: Check out the teaching station to practice setting a belay from fixed anchors and also for cleaning anchors.

name: Unnamed 5.9
description: Follow the middle of the face up through what appear to be easy holds. Watch out for those sucker holds... Route #7 on Short Stack on 2019 guide.

name: The Corner
description: Climb up through the easy overhanging corner to surmount the face. Climb the face using the arete to the right and face holds to your left to the top.

name: Dream The Impossible
description: Start on the face right of the aerie. Move left onto the arete. Climb the arete and left face directly to the top.

name: High Times
description: Sport route on Snip Block

name: Snip, Snip, Snip
description: More thin face holds and sharp edges on this one.

name: Stembellishment
description: This climb reminded many of us of how we climbed the hallways in our homes as kids --left hand and left foot on the left side wall and right hand and right foot on the right side wall.  Clip the bolts on both sides and use the anchors on the top of either "Let It Bleed" or those on top of "Heir Rider Equipped."  Fun full body stemming allows for unique body positions.  Creative and unusual for a sport climb.

name: Beginner Wall Center
description: Like it's neighbor to the right,  be prepared for a less than secure finish on this climb.  The holds going to the anchors are not as good as you would like them to be.

name: Beginner Wall Left
description: Fun sport route on Beginner Wall that has more secure clipping holds than its two brothers to the right.  It is a touch harder than H.B's Big Climb on the far right of the wall, but easier than the two routes in the middle of the wall.

name: Beginner Wall Right
description: Be prepared for a less than secure finish on this climb.  The holds going to the chains are not as good as you would like them to be.

name: Center Crack
description: Climb the obvious large crack in the center.  The crack is probably only a 5.6, but the final move to clip the anchors is harder.

name: H.B's Big Climb
description: This is the easiest sport route at The Lost Crag.  Chuck and his son Henry (Beaumont) helped clean this route, and they were the first ones to climb it.

name: Quantico
description: Climb the face just right of the crack.

name: Regalito
description: There is one bolt.

name: The Sentry
description: Boulder Climb

name: Shorty Clips (A.K.A. Dreary Day Delight)
description: Climb the sport route in the center of this face to the top.

name: Shorty Trad
description: Second of two routes on Tunnel Block (L)

name: Slacker
description: Start just right of the large ledge. Climb up and traverse left on the ledge. Clip the first bolt and climb up on large holds past the second bolt. Move left at the large ledge and step up to a pocket out left. Clip the third bolt and top out.  This climb is a sandbag at 5.6, be prepared for a 5.7+.

name: All day long (led, fell, hung)
description: A micro tcu will "protect"...lol (fair warning) up to the first bolt. Bolt clipper friendly from there. Spicy start...proceed with caution ⚠️

name: Deliverance
description: Starts below obvious flake 10' right of O'Brien's Line. Work up through balancy feet and a powerful reach to the flake over head. Move right around arete. Finish on overhanging face.

name: Easier Said Than Done
description: Start in the corner in front of Lunch rock. Follow the corner system up through bulges and the slightly overhanging face to the top.

name: O'Briens line
description: Climbs the arete feature.  Technical and balancy.  Sustained in nature. Crux above 3rd bolt

name: Piton Corner
description: Climb the inside dirty corner up past 2 pitons to the top. Better than it looks.

name: Redline
description: Begin 12' right of Easier Said than Done on the red streak. Follow the red streak up the bolt line, finishing on headwall above.

name: Split Decision
description: Climb up moderate 5.8 face holds to the first clip.  Continue up the bolt line on flakes and face holds to a large horizontal. Finishes on  larger holds above.  Steep and continuous from the first bolt up to the top.

name: Trundle Queen
description: On the left of the obvious Burner Run Roof. Starts up blocky terrain aiming left for the corner and ledge. Follow corner to top.

name: 1. Trailside
description: Stand start just right of the detached block, left hand on a weird sidepull pinch and right compressing on a bad sloper. Step on and climb up through puzzling face to top.

name: 10. Actual V2
description: Left of Sam's V2, stand start at about head height on crimps. Move up right to another crimp, and left to top.

name: 11. Ze Warmup
description: On the obvious arete, start low matched on jugs. Stand up the arete to the top.

name: 11a. Ze Crimps
description: About 4 feet left of the arete, start low in jug rail. Climb straight up face on crimps avoiding arete.

name: 12. Coming Out
description: Start down in the hole matched on a great jug ledge. Climb straight up through sidepulls and tiny holds to the top.

name: 13. I'm So Fancy
description: Sit start down under the short roof matched in a large vertical seam and reach up right hand to a jug. Climb out and left on bad holds, then do a long reach for a good vertical seam. Grab dunkers and topout.

name: 14. Grog Blossom
description: Sit start compressing on the short blunt arete with a good left heel hook. Slap your way up to the top.

name: 15. Cave Dwellers
description: In the middle of the corridor sit start on weird underclings. Climb up pure crack features to a slopey topout.

name: 16. Project
description: Sit start on the arete on often wet holds. Climb up bulging arete to a big move before the scary topout.
Start low on obvious rounded arete and climb it to the top.

name: 18. Sidewayz
description: Just right of the short mossy arete, start matched on slopey jug. Move up and right to a gaston feature, and continue to the top.

name: 19. Chinny Chin Chin
description: Stand start on opposing side pulls at about chest height. Climb tiny dihedral feature. Topout. Harder than it looks.

name: 2. Trailside Arete
description: On the more blunt of the two right aretes, start matched low on a lieback. Climb arete to the top.

name: 20. Chopping Block
description: Start low just right of the arete and climb up to the name's sake feature. Don't worry, it *shouldn't* come off when you use it to topout.

name: 21. Project
description: Probably some bad ass can find holds they can use up this beautiful blank, gently overhanging highball face.

name: 22. Project
description: The king line here at The Pyle. Anyone reading this who is Daniel Woods status, come check this thing out right meow! Just left of Child Support, an obvious blank arete.

name: 23. Child Support
description: Stand start high matched on good crimp flake. Climb straight up. Topout.

name: 24. Story Tellers
description: Stand start on decent hold about chest height below the arching dihedral. Climb up through said dihedral to a committing finish. Topout.

name: 25. Project
description: Right of Story Tellers, there is an easy start that leads up to a blank section. Looks like it can be overcome with a really big dyno or a balancy crimpy thing.

name: 27. Project
description: Cool looking face leading to a small roof at the top over a bad landing. We've never even been on this one yet, could be easy.

name: 28. Nikki's Arete
description: Climb the obvious arete left of Money Land.

name: 29. Money Land
description: At the bottom of the face / lip of the roof, start matched in big jug. Climb up through Rocktown-esque holds to the top.
Right of the small tree, stand start high on the arete with a right hand crimp left hand sidepull. Pull on and fire for better holds, then topout.

name: 30. Laura's Line
description: Climb line of jugs on the areteish thing right of Money Land.

name: 31. Put On One Day
description: In the middle of the tall face, stand start on good holds. Climb up to a big move up and right to more good holds. Topout.

name: 32. Welcome to the Pyle
description: Start on your choice of non-sense at about chest height. Climb up blunt and blank arete all the way to the top.
Cool little slab all by itself. Pretty self explanitory.

name: 34. Rhodos Grow On Bouldos
description: Sit start and climb the right arete of this small overhung boulder to an obvious topout.

name: 35. Tim's Arete
description: Start low just left of arete matched on crimps. Climb up arete till the holds run out and dyno! Or figure something else out, your choice.

name: 36. Project
description: Currently dubbed the Clit Dyno, i think you'll see why. In between two trees on the far right of the cliffline, can't miss it.

name: 37. End of the Road
description: a few feet right of the arete, sit start in good jug rail. Climb up the slab on tiny holds that face the wrong way.
Obvious arete on block with climbs that are usually wet.

name: 39. Slanters
description: In front of tree, start low on the bulgey lip right of Jorge's Crack. Make a long move up to a not so good ledge, then keep it together for the top.
Climb face

name: 40. Jorge's Crack
description: Start matched at the base of the crack on the right arete. Climb straight up and topout.

name: 41. Rubik's Cube
description: A harder than it looks beginning leads to an easier than it looks top. Sit start on good holds on the left side of a big seam. Climb up and left to a decent crimp rail on the face. Go straight up from here, avoiding the giant horn to the left.
Stand start on lowest slopers on the bulge. Avoid the detached block down and right for your feet, and climb up the bulge on cursed slopers to the top.
Climb the high face.

name: 7. Aubree's Line
description: Sit start on good jug ledge in the middle of the small face. Climb up through slanted crimps to the top.

name: 8. Lumpy Arete
description: Start low and climb the Arete left of Aubree's Line.

name: 9. Sam's V2
description: In the middle of the face, sit start in sharp pockets. Follow pure line of desperate holds to the top.

name: [Redacted]
description: Stand start about 6 feet left of arete matched on good crimp rail. Follow line of holds up and right to a difficult topout on the buldgy arete.

name: Unknown V1
description: Start matched on an obvious rail on the face. Bump up to great jugs, and get high feet. Figure out a way to throw for the overhanging lip. An aesthetic problem with fun movement.
Right of Baby Grand, start in the small dihedral feature and make your way to the slopey top.

name: 43. Baby Grand
description: Stunning blank face looming over the trail. Sit start with right hand on a big gaston and left on a bad crimp. Make a hard first move up to a decent sloper, then a worse sloper. Power up to a good but sharp ledge and topout.

name: 44. Piano Man
description: Start matched on slanted rail. Move up through some sharp holds to a crimp slot. Match in the slot and climb up to the topout.
Under roof on left side, sit start matched on right facing jugs. Climb up through slopey ledges to topout the bulge.
About 8 feet right of slanted arete, start low on your choice of cursed crimps. Climb straight up the slab, avoiding the jug ledge a little further right.

name: 50. Diamonds on the Side
description: On the left side of this face, start low matched on a triangle sloper just beneath the lip. Traverse lip up and right to a topout at the point.

name: 51. Diamonds in the Front
description: In the middle of the overhung face, sit start low in the obvious seam. Follow seam out to lip and topout up and right.

name: 52. Diamonds in the Back
description: Just left of the arete, sit start in lowest right facing jug flake. Follow line of holds up the flake to a tricky section just before the top.

name: 53. Copper Head Lane
description: An obvious line in the center of the face. Start low on good holds, follow holds up to a topout at the point.

name: 54. Copper Head Road
description: Sit start far right on this slopey lip. Traverse the lip left to topout above 52.

name: 55. The Backwards Man
description: On the slab right of Copper Head Road, Start standing on the big dead tree. Jump on and run up without using your hands.
Start matched in weird horizontal seam at abs height. Step on and get your balance to reach high to the next horizontals, and topout.
Just left of the arete, stand start on a good obvious jug. Climb straight up the face, avoiding holds on the arete to the right.
Stand start on good holds around the right side of the arete. Climb to top.

name: 59. Witness the Sickness
description: Start in small dihedral feature matched on crimps at the lip of the small roof. Move up through cursed horizontals to the top.
Start low and climb the easy arete.
Sit start just right of the arete on a crimp rail. Climb up and out the bulge, avoiding the left arete, to the top.

name: 62. The Wrong Way
description: Start just left of the roof sitting matched on a big jug ledge. Climb straight up.

name: 63. The Right Way
description: Just left of the small roof, sit start on obvious jug ledge. Follow line of crimp out and right to get some slopey jugs right of the downed tree and topout.
Right of arete stand start on lumpy jugs. Move up left to a big sidepull, and keep going to the top.
Sit start in good right facing flake. Climb straight up through a sloper and undercling crimpers on flakes.
Stand start in good vertical seam at chest height. Move through big left side pull and mantle a big slopey ledge to the top.
Stand start on bad slopers on the arete with good feet. Maneuver your way up to the good crimp on the right side, then keep going to the top.

name: Fallside
description: Climb up left side of prow using sidepulls and pinches.  Move up and right to a small edge.  Finish through notch and topout.

name: Left Hook
description: The crack following the left side of the boulder. The crux is at the top where it becomes positive.

name: Bil-Jac-Son
description: Start 10 feet right of Mellow Mood. Climb up the obvious inside corner. Hit the ledge and continue up the left-facing flake to to your right to the top of the cliff.

name: Get Up Stand Up
description: Climb up through generous holds to a tricky stance on the right tip of Loggia ledge. Make a commiting move off the ledge and up to easier climbing.  Continue left around the tree.  Finish on the flake and buckets above. Fun climbing!

name: Loggia
description: This is a highly recommended route... Climb up the short face passing the first two bolts to the base of the roof. Clip the bolt under the roof and make the commiting moves right out over the lip. Pull up to the rest ledge. Shake it out and continue up and left through the bulging crux and continue up to the comfort ledge. Finish on the short easy section to the shuts. NOTE: watch for copperheads if rigging this one on top rope. One seems to live under the rock perched on the edge of the cliff. It usually lays in the leaves on top and blends in very well. A colorful specimen of the local copperheads. Please admire, dont harm or disrupt. Thanks.

name: Mellow Mood
description: Climb up easy 5.4 moves from the ledge to the base of the overhang.  Climb through the overhang, finish on face moves to the top.

name: Prince of Darkness
description: Climb up the short face passing 2 bolts to the main larger overhang. Climb out the overhang and pull the crux at the lip to gain the rest in the blocky section above. Finish by moving up and right to the shuts under the alcove above. Fixed draws on the roof clips.

name: Shifticus
description: Climb the first three bolts of Loggia. Start heading right under the roof to the inside corner. Follow corner through several overlaps to the top.

name: Small Axe
description: Route begins 10' left of Loggia. Climb up the face to "bird poo ledge". (the white stuff is NOT chalk). Don't let this deter you from this most fun route... climb up into and out of the very fun and interesting corner to the moderate clean face climbing above.

name: Solstice aka natural selection
description: Begin just right of the blank roof. Climb the big jugs up the ever so slightly overhanging arete and roofs. Continue up through the crux to the left facing flake. Finish on easier face climbing above.

name: Unfamiliar Territory
description: An awkward weakness on the far left side of Maple Wall turned out to be an okay line. Follow the obvious weakness through some face climbing down low, to an off width section. P.S. don’t expect to get off this route looking very clean. The crack can be a little dirty.

name: The Bees Knees
description: Very fun climbing on flakes, crimps and a jug here and there.  Start can be damp several days after a rain.  The start is a little less than picturesque, but quickly turns quality.  The crux is up high on the route after the burn sets in.  Overhangs more than it looks.  Cool looking cobble rock!

name: BOP
description: Start below the large shelf that splits the wall.  Climb the shorter section up to the shelf passing 2 bolts, from the shelf move up to the bulge (crux) pull the crux and finish on laybacks to the top.

name: Carl's Bunnies
description: Quality line of SWPA gritstone.  A short but very fun route.  Worth getting on despite its short nature.  Several committing moves put you at the tricky top out.  Commit to the finishing move and success is yours.  Highly recommend.  One of the best 3 bolt routes in SWPA.

name: Petrified
description: One of the longer lines at River's End crag.  Small overhangs lead past the petrified tree the route is named after.  Crux is near top on short head wall at 5th bolt.

name: Sludge Factory
description: From the small ledge, juggle your way up the arete to a stance under a small roof (crux). Follow the bolts to a big ledge under the prominent roof. Pull the roof, and anchors are just above that.

name: Snail Trail
description: Short trad line with very good protection.  Follows inside corner to a crux top out involving some stemming.  Good climb for the grade.  Takes solid cams all the way.

name: Thieves in the Night
description: First starting moves could be considered a crux and stick clipping might be a good option. Easier climbing from bolt 1 to 2.  Sustained climbing to be found above.

name: Whale Tail
description: Great route for the new sport climbing leader.  Offers safe climbing on generous holds.  A somewhat committing, short crux section mid route.  Due to the prominent edge apprx. 8' below shuts, it is recommended to rappel from the shuts after finishing or bring a second up from the top to clean draws, then walk off to the left.

name: Arachnophobia
description: Climb the first 3 bolts of Soul Rebel to the rest ledge. At the rest ledge move right out balancy moves and up through the overhangs to the lip. Pull the lip and finish on the face above. Has its own anchors.

name: Cry Me a River
description: Climb a slightly overhanging face to a crux at the third bolt. Surmount ledge and continue up easier climbing to shuts.  Much easier than Metamorphosis and Firefly.

name: Firefly
description: Start below the first bolt, clip bolt and move right and follow the arete passing 2 more bolts.  Crux at 3rd bolt. Finish at ring shuts under roof.(Continuing past the shuts is Good Day to Die 5.11a)

name: Flying Dutchman
description: Fun, popular and great for a new leader.  Crux is height dependent only (kids have problems reaching the next hold), but can be avoided by moving right.  Slight rope drag when lowering from top.

name: Good Day to Die
description: Shares the same start as Firefly.  Climb firefly to the shuts.  Clip a shut and continue over the akward bulge to the face climbing above.

name: Humpty Dumpty
description: Climb start just right of the water streaks through several overhangs passing "the block that should not be" on your left. Continue up the face to the final overhangs. Finishes at the chains at the lip.

name: Kaya
description: Climb up past the first several bolts to the roof. pull the roof to the inside pink corner climb the corner up to rest ledge.  NOTE: The bolt at the large rest ledge is hard to clip for short people.  Continue up the next corner to below the main large overhang.  Traverse left across the exposed face to the clip at the point.  Pull up and over to easier climbing and the shuts above.  A super fun line, with some commiting moves.

name: Metamorphosis
description: Climb slightly overhanging face to a crux at the third bolt.  A section of easier climbing follows.  Then, continue up the short corner/crack section past the final bolt to the shuts.  This climb has seen some serious accidents. Please consider the final moves and be competent at the suggested grade.  It can be tricky and a ledge fall is the outcome if your not a solid 5.8 leader.  Proceed with caution and have fun!

name: Natural Mystic
description: Start in front of the Bent tree. Climb up the continuous overhangs to the final lip with a fixed chain draw. Pull the lip and finish on easier face climbing above. Most people stick clip the first bolt.

name: Soul Rebel
description: This is the line to the right of the bent tree. Climb up through the overhangs to the rest ledge. Climb past 2 prehung draws crux and up the final face to the anchors. (Some folks climb this route to the rest ledge and lower from the fixed chain draw 5.9+ AKA: Soul)

name: Don't Fret Over Lost Dreams
description: Linkup of 'Dreams Killed from COVID-19' to the original line of 'Don't Fret the Arete', starting at the very left (Northeast arete). An attempt to get some distance on these shorties.

name: Don’t Fret the Areté
description: After rain, this route is the first route to dry off. Start on the second block from the right and continue the block line to the top. Can clip second bolt of 'Stop Watching Television'.  Direct line goes at ~10d; if you use the arete, should be easier but a fall might be epic.

name: Dreams Killed by COVID-19
description: The north face traverse. Original start is left limited by the moss on the short end. Left to right is much harder than right to left since the crux is towards the northwest arete. A majority of the route goes at V2-/V2, but of course there are plenty of ways to make this harder. Portions of the route are usually wet, but, if you want to wait, it takes two-ish days to dry after a storm.

name: Dreams Killed from Watching Television
description: One way to make these short routes longer. This linkup route starts on 'Dreams Killed by COVID-19' (left-to-right start), then traverses directly towards the 1st bolt of 'Stop Watching Television'. Finishes on that line.

name: East End Crash
description: Support Column to the pillar; move left, move right, move up, move down, hell try doing a hundred laps around.

name: Friction Fun
description: No hard crux move like the left 5.11. Merely stout thin face climbing the whole way.

name: Is A Truth
description: Good rails everywhere, just need some strength to power through it.

name: Never Enough Chalk
description: Beta intense start. Gets easy but dirty after first bolt.    Super high ball boulder problem.

name: Pandemic Liability
description: South face of the main pillar with the original send done left to right without use of the platform edge. Once you get to the platform area, you can use it or not. Much like the other traverses, using the platform edge won't change the grade since the meat of the route is towards the start and progressively gets easier towards the right end minus one slippery cruxy move.  The name of the route comes from the (kinda) second crux near the big step, which can mess your ankles up if you botch the move. It’s often wet and your foot can easily slip off. If you have a crash pad, try to protect that move.  Fight the barn door on the finish, grabbing the opposing arete with both hands.

name: Raiders of the Lost Bolts
description: An old bolt line that appeared to be missing its hangers. If done direct, the route will feel sustained. The crux is low and is difficult to bypass. Can use the arete to ease up the final moves of the route.

name: Rail Blazzin'
description: Originally the western face of the lower pillar. This route has morphed into the route that follows the trim on the north face, west arete. The landing is promiscuous.

name: Rock Hug
description: The highest problem on the lower pillar, which will almost feel high ball. Start and end where the angled blocks meet the normal stacked blocks and finish at the top of the last block. If you use the tops of the blocks beneath the top block, this is ~V2. If you do it without, getting the top should be the hardest move.

name: Shoulder Shrug
description: Shortest of the routes on the north face, which requires some nifty foot work. The easiest path utilizes the arete.

name: Social Distancing
description: A line that traverses the lower pillar. Much like the traverse on the main pillar , the crux is near the northwest arete. Right to left is easier than left to right.

name: Stale Isolation
description: An easy boulder problem that has some heights to scare you a bit. Aretes off is a bit harder with the crux move before the top out.

name: Stop Watching Television
description: Short route two bolts. A top rope anchor should be built using the brackets on top of the pillar.    Super high ball boulder problem.

name: Throw Away Your Keys
description: Easy start. The crux comes between the 2nd and 3rd bolt. It is possible to bail to the left into a large crack which runs all the way to the top.

name: To the Top
description: Climb to/from top of the Bridge Pillar; useful for setting up TR anchors. As difficult as East End Crash.

name: Fox's Opium Den
description: Start with your feet on the low ledge and your hands pinching the intermediate ledge. From here, grab the three finger jug immediately above your face with your left hand, then blast off for the big ledge for the finish.

name: Butter Beer
description: Step on rock jutting out from the base of the outcrop, climb to the next ledge up, then edge around the corner to the left. The crux is going from that block to the top of the opposite block to your left. No hard moves or anything, just a quick little problem I played with.

name: Air Plants
description: Start the same as Almost Air Plants, but at the finish of Almost Air Plants, go to the left and figure your way to the point of the boulder.

name: Almost Air Plants
description: Use a smear for your first hold, then slot your left foot into the horizontal crack. As soon as you do this, dyno for the incut jug at the top of the boulder.

name: Fat and Ugly
description: Follow the obvious holds up to the lip of the boulder, then edge over to the top out (same as Short and Inflexible, Goddamn Chickens, and No Shit Sherlock). Finish by topping out.

name: Goddamn, Chickens
description: Thin holds, mostly smears for the footholds, but abundant holds with good spacing. Hardest part is the smears. Finish is the same as every other problem on this side for the topout.

name: Is Quaid near here?
description: Instant classic overhang with good top out.

name: Island Traverse
description: Starts on Short and Inflexible, then transitions over to Fat and Ugly and finish on its start.

name: Kinda Dumb
description: Only problem with a different end, besides Island Traverse. Follows the same holds as Goddamn, Chickens with a different variation ending.

name: No Shit Sherlock
description: Really no crux. Just a fun, easy warmup problem.

name: Randy Moss
description: Start where the overhang meets the face with a pinch heel and side pull. Slap a slopper and find a crimp. Mossy topout.

name: Short and Inflexible
description: Starts off on a little ledge. If you're short (like me), dyno for the second hand hold. Smear with your right foot and stem with your left. Finish is tricky, as you have to grab a not so obvious pinch/undercling to shift your balance for the top out.

name: Walking with Quaid
description: start on sloper rail and a crimp with an okay toe a in pocket and a toe hook for the start. work up through slopers and crimps the over the the arete and a jug up to the top out.

name: X-Men
description: Start matched on diagonal rail, good foot and heel hook up to a shouldery flat sloper ledge up through some crimps then the top out it basically Air Plants. Kind of.

name: End Wall
description: Easy route, a few pinches. The one rock looks sketchy, but in reality is very stable. most challenging part is popping up through the Rhododendron bush at the top of the route.

name: Hmmmm I Don't Know
description: Quick line that we put up in the rain, using the trad gear for the first time. It's found at the end of the cliff, around the corner from End Wall (V1). follows a crack line up some crazy features eroded into the sandstone. The route starts in a little alcove that you have to pull yourself up into, then follows the fin to the left of the alcove.

name: Shit!
description: The route follows a series of huecos up the face to a large ledge, then traverses over to the end of Cold Shut (5.8). The crux comes in the first ten feet, before the ledge. Very small footholds and slippery handholds (we did it while it was raining), along with mud on the ledge just compounds the difficulty of the route. IF TOPROPING WITH COLD SHUT ANCHOR: BE CAREFUL. ALL FALLS WILL SWING YOU BACK AGAINST THE WALL WHERE COLD SHUT IS!!!

name: Crimp on the Barby
description: Easy boulder route, more hand work than foot work. Follow the line of crimps and ledges up the middle of the face. Very fun to send, with a fun little top out. Hardest part would be getting up over the little bulge after the second ledge.

name: Of Mice and Men
description: SDS at the base of the blunt arete. Work up into underclings and then the seam above. Get your feet way up and make a huge reach to a good hold at the lip the boulder.
